9b66083788581c264a097e26795561cb3eac455d

I know people aren't fans of macros so this will probably be shut down, but this pattern appears often enough to almost warrant a `READWRITEIF(condition, ...)`. Above cases would be
```C++
READWRITEIF(!(s.GetType() & SER_GETHASH), VARINT(_nVersion, VarIntMode::NONNEGATIVE_SIGNED));
...
READWRITEIF(obj.nStatus & (BLOCK_HAVE_DATA | BLOCK_HAVE_UNDO), VARINT(obj.nFile, VarIntMode::NONNEGATIVE_SIGNED));
READWRITEIF(obj.nStatus & BLOCK_HAVE_DATA, VARINT(obj.nDataPos));
READWRITEIF(obj.nStatus & BLOCK_HAVE_UNDO, VARINT(obj.nUndoPos));
```

